  <h2>FAQ</h2>

  <h3>What is iWatched?</h3>
  <p>A simple way to track the movies and shows you’ve watched, save things to revisit, and favourite your personal picks.</p>

  <h3>How do I add a title?</h3>
  <p>Use search, open the title page, then click the button to mark it as <em>Watched</em>, <em>Saved</em>, or <em>Favourited</em>.</p>

  <h3>Can I edit or remove entries?</h3>
  <p>Yes. Open an item from your profile to change notes (where available) or remove it from watched/saved/favourites.</p>

  <h3>What’s the difference between Watched, Saved, and Favourited?</h3>
  <p><strong>Watched</strong> logs that you’ve seen it, <strong>Saved</strong> bookmarks it for later, and <strong>Favourited</strong> highlights the titles you love.</p>

  <h3>Do I need an account?</h3>
  <p>Yes—an account is required to save your activity and manage your profile.</p>

  <h3>Is it free?</h3>
  <p>Yes. Core tracking features are free. Some optional features may evolve over time.</p>

  <h3>Where does your data come from?</h3>
  <p>Posters and metadata are provided by The Movie Database (TMDb). This product uses the TMDb API but is not endorsed or certified by TMDb.</p>

  <h3>How is my data used?</h3>
  <p>Only to operate iWatched. See our <a href="/policy/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> and <a href="/policy/terms-of-service">Terms of Service</a>.</p>

  <h3>Can I import/export my data?</h3>
  <p>Export and import are on the roadmap.</p>

  <h3>I can’t find a title—why?</h3>
  <p>It may be missing from TMDb or listed under a different regional title. Try alternate names or check TMDb directly.</p>

  <h3>How do I report incorrect info?</h3>
  <p>Use the “Report” link on a title page (goes to TMDb), or contact support.</p>
